BORED is a card game where players seek to make sets of cards:

Three or more of the same number and diffeerent colors;
Three or more of the same color and consecutive numbers;
Five letter cards that spell out B-O-R-E-D.

Shape cards and instructional cards alter the flow of play or the construction and value of sets.

The long-term goal is to earn the five letters BORED on the "scorebored".  Each hand that a player ends by making a B-O-R-E-D set is worth one letter; points accumulated through making numeric sets and straights can be used to buy more letters toward the win.

Word Twist is a game for two teams.  Teams take turns drawing a card from the deck which will display one of five categories, some of which incorporate elements from other well-known word games.  The categories are:


     Nonsense - players have to answer a question on acronyms, dates, words, people or movies;
     Word Bluff - players have to identify the correct definition of a word from three possible choices;
     Express Yourself - players give clues to get their teammates to identify a word, but cannot say certain banned words;
     Word Twist - both teams compete to make as many smaller words as possible from the letters of a given word;
     Memory Time - a short passage is read from the card and questions are then asked to the opposing team.


Teams accrue points in each round and the winner is the team with the most points after a predetermined number of rounds.

From the box front: Word Twist: Every Word Game You've Ever Played - In One!

Pokemon of D is a 3-in-1 FREE print and play game (print Pokemon of D and you can play 3 different games with the components).
Pokemon of D is inspired by Slapshot (for Pokemon Tournament concept), Pokémon Trading Card Game (for Pokemon Type/Weaknesss), Pokémon Master Trainer (for the Pokemon Power and Pokemon Adventure concept).

The 3 games you can play in Pokemon of D are:
1. POKEMON TOURNAMENT (A hilarious game for 2-10 Players). The Pokemon Tournament has just begun! Each Player is a Pokemon Trainer, and each Trainer will use 6 Pokemon to compete  in the Pokemon Tournament!
2. POKEMON: TEAM ROCKET ! (A quick game for 2-4 Players). Jesse, James and Meowth from Team Rocket have made some plans to disturb the Pokemon world ! The Players are the Pokemon Trainers, and each Trainer will form a Team of Pokemon and the Team will be send to defeat Team Rocket !
3. POKEMON ADVENTURE (An adventure game in the Kanto Pokemon world for 2-5 Players, around 45 minutes if played by 3-4 players, no dice!). The Players are Pokemon Trainers. You will travel across the land, searching far and wide. You will catch Pokemon and Legendary Pokemon, collect Badges, defeat Team Rocket, then at last will face to face with the Pokemon Master in Indigo Plateau.

The complete components:
- 150 Pokemon cards {for PT, P:TR!, PA}
- 18 Team Rocket cards {for P:TR!, PA}
- 1 Map board {for PA}
- 12 Badge Token (4 are empty) {for PA}
- 5 Pokemon Master cards {for PA}
- 5 different Player Pawns, one for each Player {for PA}

If you or your kids like Pokemon, I am sure you will love this. 
We have played this for months and we bring this game everywhere we go :D

Download the game for free at: https://www.jackdgames.com/free-games.html

Game of construction of routes. The objective is to have the highest score at the end of the game. 
Players have at their disposal merchants, mercantile cities and ships. 
The first occupy the connections formed when locating a tray as well as areas on the planet (only when connection with the same color). 
With their ships, the players occupy commerce routes, that will award them VPs if connected to a planet or intersection from mercantile city.

The game uses an action points mechanic (seven points). The actions can be: 
- get a piece from the board 1AP;
- add a piece to the board 2AP;
- add a merchant 1AP;
- remove a merchant 1AP;
- add a ship to a route 1AP;
- add a mercantile city 2AP;
- change a piece in the board for another one 2AP;

The game finishes when the last piece is added to the board by a player. Score is then tallied and the winner is the player with most VP. The game is of easy learning, fast and very competitive, demands good capacity of observation to find the best oportunities for scoring.


Jogo de constru&ccedil;&atilde;o de rotas, cujo objetivo &eacute; somar a maior pontua&ccedil;&atilde;o ao final da partida.
Para tal tem a disposi&ccedil;&atilde;o mercadores, cidades mercantis e naves. Os mercadores s&atilde;o usados nas conex&otilde;es formadas ao posicionar a pe&ccedil;a de tabuleiro. Sobre o planeta somente se a cor da conex&atilde;o corresponder a uma das cores do planeta. J&aacute; as naves os jogadores ocupam uma rota de com&eacute;rcio, que s&oacute; poder&aacute; ser pontuada ao fechar a rota com uma pe&ccedil;a de planeta ou interse&ccedil;&atilde;o para cidade mercantil. As cidades mercantis s&atilde;o posicionadas sobre tabuleiros com interse&ccedil;&otilde;es de rotas, onde houver a presen&ccedil;a de um circulo tracejado identificando a condi&ccedil;&atilde;o. 
O jogo funciona utilizando a mec&acirc;nica de pontos de a&ccedil;&atilde;o (sete pontos).

As a&ccedil;&otilde;es podem ser:
-pegar uma pe&ccedil;a de tabuleiro - 1PA;
-posicionar uma pe&ccedil;a de tabuleiro - 2PA;
-posicionar um mercador - 1PA;
-posicionar uma nave sobre a rota - 1PA;
-posicionar uma cidade mercantil - 1PA;
-retirar mercador j&aacute; posicionado - 1PA;
-trocar  pe&ccedil;a de tabuleiro por outra - 2PA;

A partida termina quando a &uacute;ltima pe&ccedil;a de tabuleiro for posicionada por um dos jogadores. &Eacute; feita ent&atilde;o a pontua&ccedil;&atilde;o final, vence quem somar a maior pontua&ccedil;&atilde;o na escala de pontos de vit&oacute;ria (PV).

O jogo &eacute; de f&aacute;cil aprendizado, r&aacute;pido e muito competitivo, exige boa dose de observa&ccedil;&atilde;o por parte dos jogadores, para explorar as melhores oportunidades de pontua&ccedil;&atilde;o.
