A dexterity game for 2-4 players, with a tree and 30 cubes.
Roll 2 dice, then use a cube to lengthen your giraffe's neck, according to the colour and the special action of the 2 dice.
Special actions:
- put the neck on the top of your giraffe;
- put the neck on the bottom of your giraffe;
- put the neck on the top of your giraffe, without using the thumb;
- lift the giraffe over the table, put the neck on the top;
- steal the neck from an opponent (you will take the coloured neck and the other necks over it).
The player who reaches the leaf on the tree wins.

V&iacute;deo Disney is a brazilian trivia game based on the movies and characters of the Disney Universe.

Each player gets 10 cards, numbered 1-10, and 3 rubber tokens. In turns, players must:
- without looking, get one card from the player to his right. This card will represent the question number and the number of spaces the player will advance if he answer correctly;

- get another card from the same player. This card number will represent the number of spaces the player will go back if he doens't answer correctly;

- the player who had his cards taken then gets one quesion card, and read the question with the number picked by the player;

- he answers the question, or spend a rubber token to get a different question, and then advances or go back as mentioned before. After that, the player get his number cards back.

The first player to cross the board wins!

Objective: be the first bringing the treasure (to be found by you or others) back home
 - moving by turn - 
 - there's a treasure (= crystal) - in Hamburg or elsewhere -  hidden on the map (one of those flipped markers);
 - roll the dice, move & find it;
 - but prepare yourself in advance with counter/marker to escape (lightning) or defense/fighting ones, because your opponents are going to hunt you;
 - bring it back to your starting place in order to win.
Content:
1 board, 4 meeples, 36 marker/counter, 2 dice, rule sheet

Objective: be the first player to reach the Check Out after collecting one grocery disc for each item on your shopping list
 - moving/acting by turn -
spin & move according to the number along the trail; you may move forward or backwards, but in one direction only;
collect grocery discs, spread on the trail (only those, which are on your list);
meeting another player (ending on the same space) you may pick one disc from him/her;

RotVar! is a board game where two or more players challenge each other directly on the battlefield.
Play as the brave Humans or the noble Arverians, the keepers of the forest.
The game consists in a series of turns where the two factions alternating between quest and battles to the death.
Fight battles that involve dozens of friends or play face to face with your enemy!
Complete missions to earn gold, which is useful to buy all that you need to crush the enemy forces:
potions, weapons, armor, spells and skills.
Earn fame, useful to recruiting new characters to make your party more complete and destructive.

RotVar! does not have the usual races, The territory introduces new creatures and monsters.

In the basic version, you'll find the tokens of Humans, of the Arverians and the monsters;
The respective sheets with the parameters;
The cards of the weapons, armor, spells and skills;
The customizable board of the battles;
The map of the world;
The rules;
The manual of the battles.

Three different modes:
Skirmish -> 15-45 min
Adventure -> 3-4 hours
Campaign -> 8-12 hours

Objective: score most winning points (after agreed time)
by acting successfully as a manager
 - acting by turn -
each player becomes a manager during a whole turn (probably several times):
during his/her management phase player is challenged (by cards)
 - red = event cards (draw and act until a blue card is drawn)
 - blue = task card
manager must announce his task and distribute (hidden) the roles cards (printed on the blue card);
now it's time to perform and deliver within a certain time (hour glass) - and afterwards each player has to vote (hidden) according to his/her specific role;
due to performance manager has several options increasing the score (betting) or finding the 'bastard'(additional points);

London is in shock! Charles Goode, headman of the Times, has just been adbucted. There's no time to lose to find him alive.

Sherlock Holmes counts on you to defeat Faust's evil plans and solve this mysterious case&hellip;

This expansion to the 2011 edition of Sherlock Holmes Consulting Detective contains 1 Case book and 1 newspaper.

Children's card game.

Every player gets five cards. A random card starts the discard stack. Each player must try to add a card to the stack. It must either be the same colour or the same number. Next player does the same and so on. If a player cannot make a legal play, he draws a card from the deck and adds it to his hand. The first player to use all their cards, wins.

To spice the game up, any player can play an Action Card to the discard pile in their turn. This causes annoyances such as;
Next player misses a turn;
Next player draws a card from the deck;
You can choose the colour that the next player must play to;
All players jump to their feet and make the sound of the animal currently on top of the discard pile. The first to do so is alright but all the other players must draw a card.
And their are further action cards than these examples.
